body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

Similar to #1503 but I am not using Docker, I am using Anaconda (in Windows), and Python is already v3.8. I am using the current version of the provided environment files. 

### Operating System

Windows 10

### DeepLabCut version

I am not able to `import deeplabcut` so I can't be sure. Might be a good idea to include a txt file that plainly lists the version?

### DeepLabCut mode

multi animal

### Device type

cpu

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Install Anaconda
2. `git clone https://github.com/DeepLabCut/DeepLabCut.git`
3. `cd` into `conda-environments` folder and `conda env create -f DEEPLABCUT.yaml`
4. `conda activate DEEPLABCUT`
5. `ipython`
6. `import deeplabcut`
